A question on what we should do with PCIe Slots..

What!? we aren't registering PCIe Slots 
https://github.com/openbmc/bmcweb/blob/master/redfish-core/lib/pcie_slots.hpp#L233C13-L233C35

https://github.com/openbmc/bmcweb/commit/7691cc2f7ef1f0ceedf3de0554045a614f25776d did.. so it got blasted somehow.

Oh, it got reverted https://github.com/openbmc/bmcweb/commit/e825cbc8f967e54dfd6d911ebbbc6b2bfc7bc543 and then you fixed the compile here:
https://github.com/openbmc/bmcweb/commit/4ce2c1b55617262e497164ebed001509d5ce8a60

Redfish moved away from pcie slots schema.. 
I think it is best if we don't register it, but then removing it here means it isn't getting compiled. I wonder if we should continue with the current code here..

Something like https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/bmcweb/+/62073 I think should be our future direction
I am okay with this because I don't see where pcie_slots is the future direction

Yep, I probably could've added that backtrace to the commit message, but if we want to add it back, that would be a different commit.  After this, (and when we get clang 18) we can actually turn on header checking in tidy.
